6. Liability rules regarding electronic conclusion of agreements
:SKRSLUT.
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
6.1 The customer is liable for losses incurred by &BANKNAVN.' due to
unauthorised use of &WEBSYSNAVN. for electronically concluding and
approving agreements if the customer has acted in a negligent manner giving
rise to liability under the general rules of Danish law, including in
particular where the customer, contrary to the rules on use of NemID
applicable from time to time, has disclosed his or her personal security
details to the person who has performed or enabled the unauthorised use.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
6.2 &BANKNAVN. is only liable for the customer's loss due to the
unauthorised use of &WEBSYSNAVN. for electronically concluding and
approving agreements if &BANKNAVN. has acted in a negligently manner
giving rise to liability under the general rules of Danish law.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
6.3 Even in situations subject to stricter liability, &BANKNAVN. is not
liable for any loss caused by the circumstances set out in clauses 5.4 to
5.6.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
6.4 Furthermore, &BANKNAVN. is in no event liable for indirect losses
suffered by the customer, including operating loss, loss of interest, loss
of time, loss of goodwill or for damage to the customer s property,
including loss of data or programs, not even if such damage is due to a
defect in &BANKNAVN. s product. This applies irrespective of whether
&BANKNAVN. has been informed of the risk of such loss, or whether
&BANKNAVN. has acted negligently.
